$ chown: sambamount:developers /srv/sambashare
$ chmod 2775 /srv/sambashare -> setgid, files created in the directory are automatically owned by the operators group.
Everybody has read access to the directory but only the marketing group has write access.

$ chmod 2770 - developers group has full access to the directory and other users have no access to the directory.

- Configure Samba

$ vi /etc/samba/smb.conf

[global]
        workgroup = MYWORKGROUP
        smb encrypt = required     -> activate traffic encryption
        server min protocol = SMB3 -> defined the minimun SMB version
        security = usr             -> control how samba autthenticate clients

[devdata] -> share named 
        path = /srv/developers.    -> the path of the share
        valid user = sambamount, @developers -> restricts access to specific users
        write list = @developers   -> Users not listed have read-only access.
        writable  = yes / no      -> authenticated users have read/write access to the share, default is no


- Protect the share so that the sambamount user has read access and the members of the developers group have read/write access. Other users must not be able to access the share.

valid user = sambamount, @developers
write list = @developers

- Protect the share so that everybody can access it, but only members of the marketing group have write access.

write list = @marketing

